This paper deals with the problem of human pose estimation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes improvements to the Mixture of Parts model, which is a popular approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of data-efficient methods, which is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of symmetric limb localization, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and other fields that deal with physical interactions.
